<br>
The Russians had a lot of people, but they weren't well armed or well trained, and their economy, being communist, was pretty weak.  Like Roggel says though, each added country required more troops to subdue on an ongoing basis as they didn't support the war.  It does seem unreasonable to think that a country as small as Germany could have conquered and held all of Europe long term, even in the absence of outside help to either side.<br>
<br>
In the end, I think that the war probably would have been won without any one of the 3 major allied powers (i.e. without England, without Russia, or without the US).  It probably would have been a much longer war.  The main threat also was that Hitler might have made an atomic bomb if he had had more time.  The Germans were working on it, but the US was way ahead of them.<br>
